verses.verse: (A Psalm of David.) Ascribe <WH3051> to the Lord, <WH3068> O sons <WH1121> of the mighty, <WH410> Ascribe <WH3051> to the Lord <WH3068> glory <WH9202> and strength. <WH5797>
Ascribe <WH3051> to the Lord <WH3068> the glory <WH9202> due to His name; <WH8034> Worship <WH7812> the Lord <WH3068> in holy <WH6944> array. <WH1927>
The voice <WH6963> of the Lord <WH3068> is upon the waters; <WH4325> The God <WH410> of glory <WH9202> thunders, <WH7481> The Lord <WH3068> is over <WH5921> many <WH7227> waters. <WH4325>
The voice <WH6963> of the Lord <WH3068> is powerful, <WH3581> The voice <WH6963> of the Lord <WH3068> is majestic. <WH1926>
The voice <WH6963> of the Lord <WH3068> breaks <WH7665> the cedars; <WH730> Yes, the Lord <WH3068> breaks <WH7665> in pieces <WH7665> the cedars <WH730> of Lebanon. <WH3844>
And He makes Lebanon <WH3844> skip <WH7540> like <WH3644> a calf, <WH5695> And Sirion <WH8303> like <WH3644> a young <WH1121> wild <WH7214> ox. <WH7214>
The voice <WH6963> of the Lord <WH3068> hews <WH2672> out flames <WH3852> of fire. <WH784>
The voice <WH6963> of the Lord <WH3068> shakes <WH9123> the wilderness; <WH4057> The Lord <WH3068> shakes <WH9123> the wilderness <WH4057> of Kadesh. <WH6946>

The voice <WH6963> of the Lord <WH3068> makes the deer <WH355> to calve, <WH9123> And strips <WH2834> the forests <WH9194> bare, <WH2834> And in His temple <WH1964> everything <WH3605> says, <WH559> "Glory! <WH9202>"
The Lord <WH3068> sat <WH3427> [as King <WH4428>] at the flood; <WH3999> Yes, the Lord <WH3068> sits <WH3427> as King forever. <WH5769>
The Lord <WH3068> will give <WH5414> strength <WH5797> to His people; <WH5971> The Lord <WH3068> will bless <WH1288> His people <WH5971> with peace. <WH7965>
